I'm not sure what you mean but I'll assume you mean in video games...<br>
Most programs you save a picture into one file..as a set of frames...I wrote a program to write sprites once...but when my computer went silly I lost it and never got around to re-doing it...<br>
you can also save the different frames into different files...I had a teacher that did this...it's good if you're swapping frames in and out and changing the animations length...it makes it pretty flexible...but it gets really unweildly for larger projects...<br>
Most RPG's you'll see one file for a bunch of animations and tiles...usually a file for each area of the game...<br>
The basic idea is that you make a pic for each movement...normally it's really really minimalistic...each frame has a defined size so that the program can easily divide them up to be useful...as well normally they have a transparency color which is usually something unnatural and bizzare like bright pink...<br>
